Space Rangers quest primer:
- These quests are branching narratives with numbered choices. Some choices advance the mission, some fail instantly, and some loop back to earlier states.
- Common situations include resource management, NPC negotiations, combat tradeoffs, and exploration or travel choices.
- Repeated scenes often signal a loop, so avoid retrying the same action unless the text gives a new clue.
- Watch the story text for concrete hints about danger, requirements, and hidden conditions. Some options are traps that end the quest immediately.
- Cautious, information-gathering actions often outperform aggressive gambles unless the text clearly rewards speed or force.
- Most quests take a specific path through 10-50 decision points, so steady progress matters more than heroics.

